HEADWORD: Exsanguious
<hw>Ex*san"gui*ous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>exsanguis</ets>; <ets>ex</ets> out + <ets>sanguis</ets>,
<ets>sanguinis</ets>, blood. Cf. <er>Exsanguineous</er>.]</ety>
<sn>1.</sn> <def>Destitute of blood.</def> <rj><au>Sir T.
Browne.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Zo⟦oum⟧l.)</fld> <def>Destitute of true, or red,
blood, as insects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

